<https://w3id.org/synapse/amp-als/vocab/dynamic%20light%20scattering> linkml:description "Dynamic Light Scattering (DLS), also known as photocorrelation spectroscopy, is a method for determining the size distribution of a sample of small particles in solution by illuminating the sample with a light source (usually a laser) and measuring the time-dependent fluctuations in the intensity of the scattered light caused by Brownian motion." ;
    linkml:meaning "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHMO_0000167"^^xsd:anyURI .

