<https://w3id.org/synapse/amp-als/vocab/electrochemiluminescence> dcterms:source "https://www.mesoscale.com/en/technical_resources/our_technology/ecl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    linkml:description "A method in which electromagnetic radiation, in the form of light emission, is generated from an electrochemical reaction in a solution." ;
    linkml:meaning "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_C111193"^^xsd:anyURI .

<https://w3id.org/synapse/amp-als/vocab/electrophoretic%20light%20scattering> dcterms:source "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electrophoretic_light_scattering"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    linkml:description "Subtype of dynamic light scattering, used to measure electrophoretic mobility." .

<https://w3id.org/synapse/amp-als/vocab/elevated%20plus%20maze%20test> linkml:description "A method which utilizes an experimental apparatus consisting of four arms, usually two enclosed and two open, in the shape of a plus (+) upon which the test animal can walk. The maze is elevated a set distance, for example 40 to 60 centimeters, above the floor or platform upon which the apparatus sits." ;
