<https://w3id.org/synapse/amp-als/vocab/gait%20measurement> linkml:description """Quantification of some aspect of a person's gait such as rhythm, variability or step length
""" ;
    linkml:meaning "http://www.ebi.ac.uk/efo/EFO_0007680"^^xsd:anyURI .

<https://w3id.org/synapse/amp-als/vocab/gb> dcterms:source "https://fairsharing.org/833"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    linkml:description "GenBank Sequence Format (GenBank Flat File Format) consists of an annotation section and a sequence section. The start of the annotation section is marked by a line beginning with the word \"LOCUS\". The start of sequence section is marked by a line beginning with the word \"ORIGIN\" and the end of the section is marked by a line with only \"//\"." .

<https://w3id.org/synapse/amp-als/vocab/gct> linkml:description "Tab-delimited text files of GenePattern that contain a column for each sample, a row for each gene, and an expression value for each gene in each sample" ;
    linkml:meaning "http://edamontology.org/format_3709"^^xsd:anyURI .

<https://w3id.org/synapse/amp-als/vocab/gel%20filtration%20chromatography> linkml:description """'Gel filtration chromatography (synonym: gel permeation chromatography - GPC) is a type of size-exclusion chromatography (SEC), that separates analytes on the basis of size, typically in organic solvents.  The technique is often used for the analysis of polymers.'
""" ;
    linkml:meaning "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHMO_0001011"^^xsd:anyURI .

<https://w3id.org/synapse/amp-als/vocab/gel%20permeation%20chromatography> dcterms:source "https://www.agilent.com/cs/library/primers/Public/5990-6969EN%20GPC%20SEC%20Chrom%20Guide.pdf"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    linkml:description "AKA size exclusion chromatography (GPC/SEC), this assay is a type of high performance liquid chromatography used to determine the molecular weight distributions of polymers." .

<https://w3id.org/synapse/amp-als/vocab/geneExpression> linkml:description "The analysis of levels and patterns of synthesis of gene products (proteins and functional RNA) including interpretation in functional terms of gene expression data." ;
    linkml:meaning "http://edamontology.org/topic_0203"^^xsd:anyURI .

